<span id="freeTextContainer5030543272950411013"><strong>American Sniper</strong><br/><br/>A very good story....it was page turner. The strong points were the view points regarding the Vietnam war....as well as how it tied together with activities &quot;back home&quot;. I appreciated the discretion Mr DeStefanis used in intimate scenes, but I firmly believe less is more regarding foul language. I understand certain characters are going to be loose with language, but plenty of writers have excellent stories by limiting it or referring to it in a generic way.<br/></span>
  <span id="freeText5030543272950411013" style="display:none"><strong>American Sniper</strong><br /><br />A very good story....it was page turner. The strong points were the view points regarding the Vietnam war....as well as how it tied together with activities "back home". I appreciated the discretion Mr DeStefanis used in intimate scenes, but I firmly believe less is more regarding foul language. I understand certain characters are going to be loose with language, but plenty of writers have excellent stories by limiting it or referring to it in a generic way.<br /></span>
